## Commit Messages

Always generate commit messages following Conventional Commits format, enforced by commitlint.

Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>

[optional body]

Allowed types (only these): feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore, ci, build, revert

Rules:
- type: required, lowercase only
- scope: optional, wrap in parentheses, lowercase or UPPERCASE
- subject: required, max 72 chars; if the full description exceeds 72 chars, keep subject concise and move extra detail into the body
- body: add a body whenever the subject alone cannot fully describe the change; blank line before it, wrap lines at 120 chars, use bullet points with "-" for multiple items
- footer: optional, blank line before it, lines max 100 chars

Examples:
  feat(auth): add email verification on signup
  fix(api): handle null session on token refresh
  chore(deps): update next to v15.3

  refactor: update project structure and improve configurations

  - Updated lint-staged commands to use pnpm
  - Added VSCode workspace settings
  - Refactored proxy function to use arrow syntax
  - Improved error handling in forms
  - Fixed environment variable handling in Supabase client
